olive oil
2 potato
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
2 tomato
1 sachet Mexican Fiesta spice blend
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet beef mince
1 egg
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
2 Butter Burger Buns

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into wedges.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle over the garlic &
herb seasoning, season with salt and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then
bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice tomato.
• In a medium bowl, combine the slaw mix, coriander, mayonnaise and a
drizzle of white wine vinegar. Season to taste.

SPICY! The spice blend is hot, use less if you're sensitive to heat.

• In a medium bowl, combine beef mince, the egg, fine breadcrumbs,
Mexican Fiesta spice blend and a generous pinch of salt. Shape beef
mixture into evenly sized patties slightly larger than your burger buns. You
should get 1 patty per person.
• Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
Cook beef patties until just cooked through, 4-5 minutes each side.

• While the patties are cooking, bake burger buns directly on a wire oven rack
until heated through, 3 minutes.
• Slice burger buns in half. Top buns with slaw, a Mexican beef patty and some
tomato.
• Serve with garlic and herb potato wedges.